{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "UpDown (Anderson et al., 2018) introduces underlying and top-level attention mechanisms, proposes trainable underlying features, and combines the attention mechanism with the language model.",
    "Adaatt (Lu et al., 2017) introduces visual flags to guide the allocation of attention, proposes an adaptive attention mechanism, and builds an end-to-end generative model.",
    "ShowTell (Vinyals et al., 2015) utilizes attention mechanisms and employs Multilayer Perceptron (MLP) as generators, combining CNN and LSTM.",
    "FC (Rennie et al., 2017) uses a CNN-encoded image as input to predict the second word.",
    "Instead of using a static spatial pool representation of the image, the attention model in Att2in (Dosovitskiy et al., 2020) dynamically reweights the input space (CNN) feature to focus on a specific area of the image at each time step."
  ],
